This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at a West Virginia Chamber of Commerce event. Pence addresses the ongoing response to Hurricane Harvey and praises the efforts of federal, state, and local officials, as well as volunteers. He also encourages Congress to pass additional funding for federal disaster assistance and asks businesses to support organizations providing aid to hurricane victims. Pence then discusses President Trump's proposed tax cuts, highlighting the need for a simpler and fairer tax code, lower tax rates for working families and businesses, and the repatriation of overseas corporate profits. He emphasizes that tax cuts are essential for economic growth and job creation. Pence concludes by expressing confidence that, with the help of West Virginia's leaders and businesses, historic tax cuts will be passed and America will become prosperous again.